          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Cross sections were calculated from the activation",
                "equation for thin foils. After the AEOB was obtained",
                "from HPGe, the cross section is sigma=AEoB/(I*n*x*(1 -",
                "exp(-lambda*tirrad))), where I is the number of",
                "incident particles per unit time, n is the target",
                "nuclei per unit volume, x is the target thickness,",
                "lambda is the radionuclide decay constant, and tirrad",
                "is the irradiation time."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " All uncertainties in this work correspond to",
                "values within one standard deviations of the mean.",
                "The uncertainty in measured radionuclide activities",
                "was calculated by the standard deviation of the",
                "activities measured in each of several HPGe",
                "measurements. These standard deviations are larger",
                "than the uncertainties calculated by error",
                "propagation of individual activity uncertainties,",
                "resulting in overall EoB 71As activity uncertainties",
                "of 2-11%. The uncertainties of counting (0.3-11%) ,",
                "foil thickness (3.6%), abundance (2.7%) , detector",
                "efficiency (2.2-2.6%), and beam intensity (3-11%)",
                "were considered for the uncertainty of cross section",
                "measurements by error propagation."
              ]
            },
